The paper deals with natural language processing and deep learning models, specifically Long Short Term Memory networks (LSTMs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the mechanism by which LSTMs come to their conclusions, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG and cs.AI likely categories as well. The paper also uses quantitative validation and pattern recognition, which are common in neural networks and computational neuroscience, making cs.NE a possible category. Finally, the paper mentions sentiment analysis, which is a common application of natural language processing, and question answering, which involves computer vision and image processing, making cs.CV a possible category.
